name: Yvette

identifying_info.employment_status: currently active in speech club as vice president of membership

behavioral: hesitancy to embrace leadership roles due to self-doubt

mental_status: Yvette is articulate and communicates well verbally, with good insight into her tendencies toward self-doubt. She expresses emotions of relief and breakthrough when new concepts are understood.
best_lifetime_functioning: Yvette has succeeded in roles that require organization and leadership, fulfilling the role of vice president of membership for her speech club without preparation and to positive acclaim.
history_of_psychological_problem_impact: Yvette expresses a history of setting unrealistically high expectations for herself, impacting her ability to recognize and appreciate her achievements and intelligence.
history_of_psychological_care: Current CBT sessions are focused on self-appreciation and acknowledging personal talents and capabilities.
personal_history: Yvette is a mother with sons who have left home; she's transitioning into a phase of life focused more on her personal growth and interests.
